After a thoroughly enjoyable Hogmanay party with some dear old friends, and a January 1st mostly spent nursing a hangover, I decided to blow off the cobwebs today by heading up Duncolm and The Slacks once again. It's certainly not the wildest or most challenging of walks, but I can get to the start point in fifteen minutes via train if the mood takes me, and the weather today was too nice to ignore! There was even a little winter fungi in the form of frosted Jelly Ears and Hairy Curtain Crust. 

Back to the grindstone tomorrow, with 2023 shaping up to be a busy year.

#hillwalking #hill #hills #kilpatrickhills #scotland #hiking

A memory from Cradle's recent Euro tour. Apart from a couple of shows with @fittowork_band and @massaokescotland in December, I've mostly been writing. This affords its own pleasures (when the juice is properly flowing), but I must admit I'm starting to miss the buzz of being on stage. It'll come soon enough, I'm sure.

By the way, check out my old playthroughs and signature bass by tapping the link in my bio. When my duties calm down a little I'll get some fresh videos on the go, so let me know, what would you like to see/hear?

We are getting ready to haunt the US again on our first tour of 2023… this time co-headlining with the devilish fiends from @devildriver, and supported by @blacksatellite and @theoniband. 🦇

You don’t want to miss these shows, they’re going to be doubly wicked!

Cradle of Filth are proud to reveal our new track “She is a Fire”, and to announce our first live album in 20 years, “Trouble And Their Double Lives”!

Watch the new music video for “She is a Fire” on YouTube (link in our bio). “Trouble And Their Double Lives” drops April 28, 2023 via @napalmrecordsofficial, featuring classics, fan favourites and two brand new studio tracks! Pre-order link also in our bio!

Recorded between 2014 and 2019 at different performances in the USA, Europe, Australia and beyond during our “Cryptoriana World Tour” and dates following, the album serves as a time-capsule of blisteringly intense live energy, and an astounding testament to Cradle of Filth’s renowned latest era. 

Produced, mixed and mastered by Scott Atkins at Grindstone Studios in Suffolk, England with recording captured by Danny B, the brand new live onslaught not only features a slew of fan favourites encompassing the band’s electrifying discography - such as “Nymphetamine (Fix)”, “Bathory Aria” and “Blackest Magick in Practice” - but also two bonus tracks and two entirely brand new songs, “She is a Fire” and “Demon Prince Regent”.

Listen to the brand new, spine-tingling studio track, “She is a Fire”, and watch its new accompanying music video today! 

And don’t forget we are just a week away from embarking on the first leg of our co-headliner “Double Trouble Live” tour with groove metal pioneers @devildriver! Support acts on the tour are @blacksatellite and @theoniband, and tickets for shows and VIP upgrades are also linked in our bio!

I decided to change things up on this tour and bring out the awesome Darkglass Microtubes X Ultra, and now I'm wishing I'd done it sooner! With the low end compressor and high end drive, it's just that bit easier to dial in the exact tone I want, with all the clank, but plenty of note clarity too. I have to reign myself in with the drive actually, because this thing can get very brutal.

Tonight we're at Amplified in Dallas, TX!

#darkglass #darkglasselectronics

It's been really cool getting to know the people of @saormusic over the past week and a bit, playing three shows, culminating in a hometown performance last night in Glasgow. This one was booked in the wake of Dominion fest's cancellation, and put together at very short notice, but it was a great success. We all had a lot of fun on stage, and the crowd seemed to be really digging it too. These photos are actually from the first show I did, but the work of @arturtarczewskiphoto deserves another share!

Thanks to @andysaor, @shengiskhan, @brydo2022, @ella.zlotos.music, @kevin_storm_guitar and @joestafir88 for the warm welcome and good times.

Apart from the stunning looks, it was the inclusion of a Fishman Power Bridge, for those acoustic tones, that really grabbed my interest. This thing has a huge range of tonal options. Most importantly though, it feels great to play!

Despite being one of the most famous hills in Scotland, I'd never done the Cobbler before today. Maybe that's because I used to be exclusively about the Munros, but thankfully I've grown out of that prejudice, and had a great time on this outstanding Corbett. Not to sound like Billy Big-Bollocks, but I thought the warnings about reaching the true summit (The Needle) were maybe a bit overstated - the thick cloud of midges at the top was more distressing than the straightforward scramble. For those who don't know, there's a hole in it that you scooch through before climbing up the far side, with the manoeuvre being called 'Threading the Needle'. Fun times, and a cracking day for it! Shame about the nightmare traffic on the way home. 😖

It's been a decent week, kicked off with an outing last Monday to see the great Iron Maiden. I've lost count of how many times I've seen them before, and I had every intention of chilling near the back this time to absorb the whole thing as much as possible. However, with a belly full of my old friend Mark's patended 'blue cocktail', I lasted a few bars into the opener, 'Caught Somewhere in Time', before deciding he and I had to get down the front where the pit had just erupted. The set was a blur from that point on, but my many bruises and hoarse voice the next day would attest to the excellent time I had.

I also played my first game of football in something like ten years on Thursday, which might not seem like a big deal, but it turns out I've really missed it! I'm still a bit hobbly now, two days later, but I'm hoping an hour of running around won't have such a debilitating effect on my legs after next week's game.

It's not all been leisure though, and I've been working hard on a pair of new albums - on Wednesday we held the penultimate writing session for the first full-length Fit to Work release, which is coming along delightfully.  We've got 12/13 songs written, and recording starts at the end of the month! 

Of course, the new Cradle album is also well underway, and I'll be laying down the bass tracks about three weeks from now. After the intensity of finishing off the writing process, I was pretty glad to take a little break from it for a short while, but today I started a deep dive into the bass parts with fresh ears and renewed vigour. I'm really excited with how it's coming together.

And look, here's a photo of me playing bass to wash all this text down with! 📸 @jwvijfvinkel

#cradleoffilth #schecter #schecterguitars #darkglass #darkglasselectronics #newtone #newtonestrings #mooer #mooeraudio #fishman #dslstraps #bass #metal

The tour is a wrap! Thanks to everyone in @devildriver, @illninoofficial, @blacksatellite and @savageexistenceofficial for an awesome few weeks, as well as the Crewdle of Filth, and all the fans who came along to see us. Until next time!

📸 @emtfilms
📸 @guitartechdaddy

#cradleoffilth #devildriver #illnino #blacksatellite #savageexistence

Overjoyed to be back in Glasgow Airport again after a whole three days. Actually, I am in a pretty good mood, and hopefully the tumult of jetlag has come to an end. I'm on my way to the last Cradle show of the year, Rock Circus in the Netherlands, where we play tomorrow.

#cradleoffilth #schecter #schecterguitars #darkglass #darkglasselectronics #newtone #newtonestrings #mooer #mooeraudio #fishman #dslstraps #bass #metal #rockcircus

We found this fine gentleman at @therockcircus yesterday - Cradle of Filth alumnus James McIlroy! James was playing guitar for the band when I first joined in 2012, and gave me a warm welcome back then. It was really cool to catch up after so long.

As for the show, the fans were out in force and the pit was raging! Lots of nice people at the meet and greet afterwards as well, which proved exceedingly popular.

With that, the final Cradle show of 2023 is finished. We'll be back in February next year for our European tour with Wednesday 13.

Crowd shot by @lifeispeachypodcast

#cradleoffilth #schecter #schecterguitars #darkglass #darkglasselectronics #newtone #newtonestrings #mooer #mooeraudio #fishman #dslstraps #bass #metal

Now that I'm back home from touring, I was finally able to delve into the hefty parcel containing my new signature Hellraiser Extreme-5 in 'Cthulhu Burst', made by the fine people at @schecterguitarsofficial. This is the first time I've laid hands on a production model, as opposed to the prototype, and it looks and feels fantastic!

Pride is something I try to keep in check, but seeing my own signature on the back of the headstock, I couldn't help but feel it welling. More importantly though, since these basses have been making their way into the hands of players around the world (all of whom I deeply appreciate), I've heard nothing but great feedback. Schecter have made an exceptional instrument, and I thank my friends there for doing so.

If you're feeling enticed, tap the link in my bio for all the tech specs. The second run is in shops now!

#cradleoffilth #schecter #schecterguitars #bass #bassguitar #lowvember #metal #fishman #fishmanpickups #fishmanfluence

Great practice session this morning going over the @saormusic set, including a new song I haven't played live before. I've got my Solo-II Supreme singing beautifully with a new set of @newtonestrings - a slightly heavier gauge than I've been using previously. I'm not 100% decided, but I think I'll be sticking with them.

I'll next be performing with Saor at Winter Assault in Brighton, on the 2nd of December. Looking forward to it!

#saor #metal #guitar #schecter #schecterguitars #newtone #newtonestrings #winterassault

Went to see @blindboyboatclub in Edinburgh last night with these absolute hunks. We three Orcadians felt very 'seen' with the amount of time given over to discussing the mythology of the islands where we grew up, during a wider discussion on folk tales and mythologies from Scotland and Ireland. Selkies, Broonies, Trows, The Nuckelavee... Assipattle and the Muckle Mester Stoor Worm didn't get a mention, but the tale lives on in our hearts. 🖤

#blindboy #orkney #mythology

A cool shot by @elviramiranphoto from Cradle's last show of 2023, in the Netherlands. I'm now settling back into normal life after quite a long stint on the road. Making plans, and feeling positive about the future (when my brain is behaving).

Obviously the festive season is coming up, and if you're thinking about doing some extravagant gifting, check out the monster bass I'm playing here - it's in the shops now! Link in bio.

@wackenopenair.official holds a special place in my heart, with lots of great memories from attending with old friends and also playing there with Cradle. In fact, my second ever performance with the band was on the main stage. The pressure was on that day!

Anyway, I'm happy to say we've been asked back once again for 2024, and I'm sure it'll be a highlight in what's already shaping up to be a watershed year.

This picture is from our 2019 appearance, where a freak lightning storm forced us to play in the big tent (and it was actually great).

An excellent weekend with @saormusic to finish off my escapades for the year, headlining the sold out Winter Assault festival in Brighton. The air travel was pretty chaotic, with delays on top of delays, including a three hour wait on the runway heading down, but we made the best of it. Apparently ours was the last flight out of Glasgow that didn't get cancelled, so I guess you could say we were lucky!

The show itself was a lot of fun, as was hanging out and enjoying a few pints with everyone. Hopefully I'll be able to play some more with Saor in the near future!

3rd 📸 @greenwyvernphotography

A far-flung throwback to this day eleven years ago, playing Munich with @cradleoffilth. This was nearing the end of my first full tour with the band in 2012, which was a very formative experience for me. Being all green and wide-eyed at the time, I have a lot of vivid memories of those five weeks travelling across Europe in winter.

This photo was taken by my good friend Will, who along with @duncjwh had travelled all the way from Scotland to come and support me on my first big tour. After the show, we discovered the bar next door was selling tequila shots for one Euro, which fuelled a wholesome snowball showdown between all the bands on the bill (God Seed, Rotting Christ, Blynd) once we were finally kicked out into the biting cold.

#cradleoffilth #schecter #schecterguitars

Whoops, a wee joke backfired earlier. I haven't been dumped and I didn't sit down to Christmas dinner with the cat. He eats cat food.

Note to self: You aren't funny. Don't try.

I started writing an in-depth 2023 review and ended up boring myself, so I'll spare all of you the long version and mostly tell it in pictures (sorry for the cropping).

1. Things are going great with @cradleoffilth. Lots of shows, writing, and recording, with 2024 shaping up to be next level, including a new album release.

📸 @itsmefurby

2. Playing with @saormusic has been an absolute pleasure - all lovely people, and I'm thoroughly enjoying the chance to play some more guitar on stage.

📸 @arturtarczewskiphoto

3. @fittowork_band played a few raging shows and festivals across the UK, and there's a new album in the works.

📸 @nofiltersever

4. I also managed a pair of very fun gigs with @massaokescotland, which is always a party!

5. I broke my leg playing football, which sucked.

6. I spent another year with my girlfriend (and all our many hairy beasties), which didn't suck! In fact, today is our 5th anniversary, so that's delightful. We're drinking fizzy wine.

Happy Hogmanay, everyone!

#cradleoffilth #saor #fittowork #massaoke

I've been pretty quiet in the online world so far this year. Regular life is dominating at the moment, and I assume people aren't too interested in my tales of resealing windows, for example. 

I have been doing a good bit of practising and writing though, with the acoustic getting a lot of attention, and there's even been a small flurry of riffage to present for future Cradle.

Tonight, I'm drinking the first pint from the latest batch of Dan's Good Beer. I haven't done a stout in ages, and it's worked out pretty well.

That's all for now. 🍻

Throwback to my first gig with @saormusic at @uprising.leicester last April. It was a festival show, and a bit of a scramble to get everything set up during changeover, so there was no time to be nervous. I had a lot of fun, and the feedback from the attendees was great! Hopefully I'll get to play a few more with Saor this year.

📸 @stephentearsoffirephotography
